com.vijfhart.casus.tree

Interface Node<T extends Node<T>>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<T>, LevelComparable<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractNode, NameNode, WrapperNode

    public interface Node<T extends Node<T>>
extends LevelComparable<T>, java.lang.Comparable<T>
    A Node is an element in a Tree, with an optional parent node. All other (implied) information about a Node in a Tree are given by looping through a TreeIterator.
